verbose_text: Elicited immune response against the implant surface also thwarts the osteogenesis process by secreting cytokines such as tumor necrosis factor alfa (TNF-alpha), interleukin beta (IL-1beta) and nitric oxide (NO) which stimulate osteoclast generation and bone resorption.
